<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="168" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,1193,1758]" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1661,1686]" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Meyer" box="[322,534,1661,1686]" pageId="17" pageNumber="168" refString="Meyer, D. L., Messing, C. G. &amp; Macurda, Jr., D. B. (1978) Zoogeography of tropical western Atlantic Crinoidea (Echinodermata). Bulletin of Marine Science, 28, 412 - 441." type="journal article" year="1978">
Meyer 
<emphasis box="[403,459,1661,1685]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">et al.</emphasis>
(1978
</bibRefCitation>
, following Messing, unpublished thesis) treated 
<emphasis box="[1080,1171,1661,1685]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">N. alata</emphasis>
as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName box="[151,289,1697,1721]" class="Crinoidea" family="Antedonidae" genus="Antedon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Comatulida" pageId="17" pageNumber="168" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="pulchella">
<emphasis box="[151,289,1697,1721]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="168">N. pulchella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
following 
<bibRefCitation author="Carpenter" box="[413,610,1698,1722]" pageId="17" pageNumber="168" refString="Carpenter, P. H. (1881) The Comatulae of the Leyden Museum. Notes from the Leyden Museum, 3, 173 - 217." type="journal article" year="1881">Carpenter (1881)</bibRefCitation>
. However, additional genetic and morphological analyses are required to clarify the number of western Atlantic taxa.
</paragraph>
